	AthenaCernlib

	* src/dummyMain.f (NEVER___USED): NEW define MAIN__ for the
	stupid linker

	* GNUmakefile.in & PACKAGE:
	new targets are the common "athena" binary
	and an AthenaCernlib library which exports all the cernlib symbols
	(and the g2c implementations)

	* changed the example and exampleTDR aliases in the setup scripts
	to use the new common binary "athena".  

	* the slug-related f77 files were moved to ZebraTDRCnv

2000-09-29  Paolo Calafiura  <calaf@atlas010.cern.ch>

	* share/setup.sh: fixed bug in setting LD_LIBRARY_PATH

	* moved "common" initialization scripts and files from 
	AthenaExample/share to AthenaCommon/share. Basically now everything
	you need to run athena is installed under 
	$(installdir)/share/AthenaCommon. You only have to provide your
	jobOptions.txt file. 

